Scientists have revealed a sophisticated new dating technique shows that Little Foot , an early human forerunner unearthed in the 1990s in South Africa , is roughly 3.7 million years old .
The age of Little Foot was lived at roughly the same time as Australopithecus afarensis .
The researchers analyzed 11 rock samples from around the nearly complete Little Foot fossil skeleton from the Sterkfontein Caves to gauge its age .